Common Mistakes in Test Case Design :

ğŸš« 1. Writing vague test steps
âŒ "Enter name and submit"

âœ… "Enter a valid name in the Name field (e.g., John), then click the Submit button"

ğŸš« 2. No expected result
âŒ Test steps without knowing what to expect = pointless.

ğŸš« 3. Too much in one test case
Keep it simple and atomic.

âœ… One scenario = one test case

ğŸš« 4. Not using design techniques
Leads to poor coverage and redundant test cases

ğŸš« 5. Not considering negative tests
Always test both valid and invalid inputs

âœ… Tip: Use a checklist when reviewing:
Clarity
Expected Result
Positive + Negative
Mapping to requirement
